definition.value: A member of the class of  chalcones that is  trans-chalcone substituted by a benzyloxy group at position 4, a hydroxy group at position 2' and methoxy groups at positions 3', 4', 5' and 6' respectively.

A compound formed spontaneously from a penicillin in aqueous solution via a rearrangement which involves fission of the beta-lactam ring, formation of an oxazolone ring and cleavage of the thiazolidine ring to generate a free sulfhydryl group.
A member of the class of  coumestans that is the diacetate ester derivative of coumestrol.
A dimethoxyflavone that is the  5,7-dimethyl ether derivative of  scutellarein.
A tetramethoxyflavone that is  tangeretin in which the methoxy group at position 5 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A  methoxyflavanone that is  flavanone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5, 6, 7 and 4'.
A 3-oxo-Delta(4) steroid that is B-norcholesterol in which the 3beta-hydroxy group has been converted to an oxo group and the double bond at position 5 has been moved to position 4.
